In Python --------- we don't have char data type
             we have str data type --- we can store both char data and string data 

             To store char data and str data ---- we use symbolic notation --- ' ' OR " "


             2. String Data------"shad" --- valid 
> 'str' is one of the pre-defined class and treated as sequence Data type.

> A str is a collection of character or numeric, special symbol  data or any type of data enclosed within sequence of character within single and double quotes.

> types of str data
1. single line string data
2. multi line string data

------------------------
> single line strin data
syntax1: varname="single line string data"
syntax2: varname='single line string data'

> multi line string data
syntax1: varname="""string data1
                    string data2"""

syntax2: varname='''string data1
                    string data2'''





- str ----> alphabet, number, special symbol.

In python programming single '' quotes takes less space


To store str data ---symbolic notation " "
